---
---
<section class="section" id="research">
  <div class="container">
    <header data-animate>
      <p class="section-label">// research</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Academic Research</h2>
    </header>

    <!-- Undergraduate Thesis / IEEE Paper -->
    <article class="research-card card featured-card" data-animate data-delay="1">
      <div class="research-header">
        <div class="research-badge-row">
          <span class="research-badge badge--ieee">
            <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5zM2 17l10 5 10-5M2 12l10 5 10-5"/></svg>
            IEEE Transactions on Image Processing
          </span>
          <span class="tag tag--cyan">Under Review</span>
          <span class="research-year">2024</span>
        </div>

        <h3 class="research-title">
          Quantitative Analysis of the Impact of Image Preprocessing on the
          Accuracy of Computer Vision Models Trained for the Identification
          of Cutaneous Dermatological Diseases
        </h3>

        <p class="research-authors">
          <strong>Gabriel Mitelman Tkacz</strong>
          <span class="orcid-link">
            <a href="https://orcid.org/0009-0004-3619-4561" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" title="ORCID">
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="var(--c-cyan)" aria-label="ORCID"><path d="M12 0C5.372 0 0 5.372 0 12s5.372 12 12 12 12-5.372 12-12S18.628 0 12 0zM7.369 4.378c.525 0 .947.431.947.947s-.422.947-.947.947a.95.95 0 0 1-.947-.947c0-.516.422-.947.947-.947zm-.722 3.038h1.444v10.041H6.647V7.416zm3.562 0h3.9c3.712 0 5.344 2.653 5.344 5.025 0 2.578-2.016 5.016-5.325 5.016h-3.919V7.416zm1.444 1.303v7.444h2.297c3.272 0 3.988-2.484 3.988-3.722 0-2.016-1.284-3.722-4.094-3.722h-2.191z"/></svg>
            </a>
          </span>
          &amp; Gustavo Scalabrini Sampaio
          <span class="funding-note">· Funded by CAPES Foundation</span>
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="research-abstract">
        A systematic quantitative study evaluating the impact of image preprocessing pipelines
        on CNNs trained to classify dermatological skin diseases using the HAM10000 dataset.
        Introduced the <em>weighted alpha (α<sub>w</sub>)</em> metric to integrate computational
        cost into accuracy gain evaluation. Tested 64 distinct preprocessing combinations —
        revealing that simpler pipelines often yield superior cost-adjusted performance, and
        that baseline model accuracy fundamentally modulates preprocessing effectiveness
        (ceiling effect). Top pipeline achieved +9.5% accuracy gain with 13× computational
        efficiency advantage.
      </p>

      <details class="abstract-expand">
        <summary>Key Findings</summary>
        <ul class="findings-list">
          <li>Best single preprocessing: Equalization alone (+8% α, α<sub>w</sub> = 10.97)</li>
          <li>Best multi-step: E → CS → N achieving max gain with α<sub>w</sub> = 13.17</li>
          <li>~50% of all tested pipelines actively <em>degraded</em> model performance</li>
          <li>Denoising operations impose 6.5× baseline training overhead</li>
          <li>Ceiling effect compresses preprocessing benefits 24× near 100% accuracy baselines</li>
        </ul>
      </details>

      <div class="research-tags">
        <span class="tag">Computer Vision</span>
        <span class="tag">Image Preprocessing</span>
        <span class="tag">CNNs</span>
        <span class="tag">Dermatology AI</span>
        <span class="tag">PyTorch</span>
        <span class="tag">HAM10000</span>
        <span class="tag">CADe / CADx</span>
        <span class="tag tag--purple">CUDA Accelerated</span>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Master's Thesis -->
    <article class="research-card card" data-animate data-delay="2" style="margin-top:1.25rem;">
      <div class="research-header">
        <div class="research-badge-row">
          <span class="research-badge badge--masters">
            <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M22 10v6M2 10l10-5 10 5-10 5z"/><path d="M6 12v5c3 3 9 3 12 0v-5"/></svg>
            Master's Thesis
          </span>
          <span class="tag tag--purple">In Progress · 2026–2027</span>
        </div>

        <h3 class="research-title">
          Multimodal Drone Detection System
        </h3>

        <p class="research-authors">
          <strong>Gabriel Mitelman Tkacz</strong>
          · Mackenzie Presbyterian University
          <span class="funding-note">· Funded by CAPES Foundation</span>
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="research-abstract">
        Developing a multimodal drone detection and classification system that fuses
        heterogeneous sensor data streams to achieve robust detection across varied
        environments and drone classes. The system combines deep learning–based computer
        vision with radio frequency (RF) spectrum analysis and radar signal processing,
        exploring early, late, and hybrid fusion strategies to maximize detection accuracy
        and reduce false positive rates.
      </p>

      <div class="research-tags">
        <span class="tag">Drone Detection</span>
        <span class="tag">Computer Vision</span>
        <span class="tag">Radar Signal Processing</span>
        <span class="tag">RF / SDR Analysis</span>
        <span class="tag">Multimodal Fusion</span>
        <span class="tag">Deep Learning</span>
        <span class="tag tag--cyan">Security Applications</span>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Extracurricular Research -->
    <div class="extra-research" data-animate data-delay="3">
      <h3 class="extra-title">Research Roles</h3>
      <div class="extra-grid">
        <div class="card extra-card">
          <h4>Engineering Infrastructure Coordinator</h4>
          <p class="extra-org">Student Academic League of AI &amp; Data Science · Mackenzie Presbyterian University</p>
          <p class="extra-desc">Orchestrated DevOps pipelines for ML model development and deployment; implemented synthetic data generation and continuous performance monitoring to detect model drift.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card extra-card">
          <h4>Research Assistant</h4>
          <p class="extra-org">Centre of Regulation and Democracy · Insper Research Institute</p>
          <p class="extra-desc">Applied machine learning, NLP, and web scraping to bridge computer science and legal research, streamlining juridical research processes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .research-card {
    padding: 2rem;
  }
  .featured-card {
    border-color: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.3);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(8, 14, 32, 0.98), rgba(10, 20, 45, 0.95));
  }

  .research-header { margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }

  .research-badge-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }

  .research-badge {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    padding: 0.3em 0.8em;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    border-radius: var(--radius-pill);
  }
  .badge--ieee {
    background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.15);
    border: 1px solid rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.4);
    color: var(--c-blue-300);
  }
  .badge--masters {
    background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.12);
    border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.35);
    color: #c4b5fd;
  }

  .research-year {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--c-text-3);
    margin-left: auto;
  }

  .research-title {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--c-text-1);
    line-height: 1.4;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .research-authors {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--c-text-2);
  }
  .research-authors strong { color: var(--c-blue-400); }
  .funding-note {
    color: var(--c-text-3);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .orcid-link { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; margin: 0 0.2rem; vertical-align: middle; }

  .research-abstract {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--c-text-2);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .research-abstract em { color: var(--c-blue-300); font-style: normal; font-weight: 500; }

  /* Expandable findings */
  .abstract-expand {
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .abstract-expand summary {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--c-blue-400);
    cursor: pointer;
    user-select: none;
    list-style: none;
  }
  .abstract-expand summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .abstract-expand summary::before {
    content: '+ ';
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
  }
  .abstract-expand[open] summary::before { content: '− '; }

  .findings-list {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }
  .findings-list li {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--c-text-2);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .findings-list em { color: #f87171; font-style: normal; }

  .research-tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  /* Extra research */
  .extra-research { margin-top: 3rem; }
  .extra-title {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--c-text-3);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .extra-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .extra-card h4 {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--c-text-1);
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }
  .extra-org {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--c-blue-400);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .extra-desc {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--c-text-2);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .extra-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .research-card { padding: 1.25rem; }
    .research-year { margin-left: 0; }
  }
</style>
